[2] Excess mortality comment/correction
Date: Fri 23 Oct 2020
From: Heinzpeter Schwermer <Heinzpeter.Schwermer@blv.admin.ch> [edited]


[re: ProMED COVID-19 update (447): herd immunity, USA excess mortality, WHO, global 20201021.7878076; [2] USA: excess mortality]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
First, many thanks for providing everyone with all the highly accurate and up-to-date information each day.

However, to me, there seems to be an error in the moderator's comments concerning the point "[2] USA: excess mortality." There, in the 1st sentence [the moderator] makes the rough calculation, "If you add the almost 200 000 deaths to the most recent mortality figures of slightly over 225 000 deaths, the estimated mortality directly attributable to the SARS-CoV-2 pandemic in the USA is 425 000." However, as I understand it, the number of known deaths due to COVID-19 is already included in the excess mortality figures. This leaves only the difference of "estimated 299 028 excess deaths" minus "known 216 025 deaths from coronavirus disease 2019," thus 70 000 deaths that might be attributable to additional unreported deaths due to COVID-19.

Concerning the analysis of excess deaths, I draw your attention to an EU project (https://www.euromomo.eu/) monitoring excess deaths in some European countries and regions.

--
Heinzpeter Schwermer, Dr. Med. Vet., MScVPH
