[India and the USA are still the most severely affected countries in terms of cumulative case counts and daily new case confirmations, with India in the 2nd position in terms of cumulative case counts. In the past 24 hours, the USA (85 302) and India (54 028) have maintained their dominance. A global total of 6476 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (22-23 Oct 2020).

Countries reporting more than 5000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (20 countries) include the USA, India, France (42 032), Brazil (23 016), UK (20 531), Spain (19 851), Italy (19 143), Russia (17 340), Belgium (16 746), Argentina (15 718), Czech Republic (15 258), Poland (13 632), Germany (13 476), Netherlands (9996), Colombia (8672), Ukraine (7517), Switzerland (6634), Mexico (6604), Iran (6134), and Romania (5028). A total of 13 countries reported more than 10 000 cases in the past 24 hours, 9 of which were in the European region. A total of 49 countries have reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 25 of the 47 countries reporting more than 1000 newly confirmed cases are from the European region, 10 were from the Americas region, 7 were from the Eastern Mediterranean region and 5 were from the South East Asia region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, there is an increase in case counts by 16.5%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 9.8%. Looking at the USA, daily case counts have increased by 16.4% and daily reported deaths have increased by 12.9%.

Impression: Global 7-day averages continue to increase with countries in the European region and the Americas region showing the largest increases in daily new cases counts, followed by the Eastern Mediterranean and the South East Asia regions. Note that the daily case count for today was close to half a million cases and the cumulative total has surpassed 42 million. - Mod.MPP]
